ingress from the host_3 port.\n  - Both directions fail only when host_3 is the endpoint, implicating switch_7’s host_3-facing edge treatment.\n\nEvidence on switch_7 (bmv2 logs):\n- MyEgress.check_is_egress_border: We see a configured hit for egress_port = 1 (decap happens and IPv4 is forwarded). This likely corresponds to one host-facing port (consistent with successful host_1 → host_2).\n- MyIngress.check_is_ingress_border: We see a hit for ingress_port = 4 (MPLS push applied on IPv4 ingress). This again likely corresponds to the other working host-facing port (consistent with host_2 → host_1 working).\n- There is no evidence (in the logs we captured) that the host_3-facing port is marked as:\n  - egress border (to pop MPLS and forward IPv4 to host_3), or\n  - ingress border (to push MPLS for traffic from host_3 destined to host_1).\n\nGiven host_1 ↔ host_2 works and host_2 ↔ host_3 works, the core and both physical links to switch_7 are fine. The failure isolates to switch_7’s border-role configuration for the host_3-facing port.\n\n3) Root cause\n- Incomplete or incorrect border configuration on switch_7 for the host_3-facing interface:\n  - Missing MyEgress.check_is_egress_border entry for the host_3 egress port: MPLS frames destined for host_3 are not decapsulated at egress and likely forwarded with EtherType 0x8847 toward host_3, which drops them—consistent with host_1 → host_3 failure and traceroute timeouts.\n  - Missing MyIngress.check_is_ingress_border entry for the host_3 ingress port: IPv4 packets entering from host_3 are not recognized as ingress-border traffic and thus do not have an MPLS label pushed for transit toward host_1—consistent with host_3 → host_1 failure.\n- Additional notes:\n  - We attempted to dump switch_7 control-plane tables directly; the table-dump tool returned a SyntaxError, so we relied on execution logs, which support the above inference.\n  - The fact that host_1 → host_2 decapsulates successfully at switch_7 (egress border hit on a port) and host_2 → host_1 encapsulates successfully (ingress border hit on a port) indicates that only one of the two host-facing ports on switch_7 is correctly configured as an LER edge. The host_3-facing port appears to be the one missing entries.\n\nKey findings summary\n- Anomaly: Complete loss of connectivity specifically between host_1 and host_3 (both directions).\n- Localization: switch_7, host_3-facing edge behavior (LER functions at ingress/egress for that port).\n- Root cause: Missing LER border-role table entries for host_3-facing port on switch_7 (no MPLS decap at egress, no MPLS push at ingress for that port), causing blackholing of host_1 ↔ host_3 traffic.\n\nNo remediation is provided per request.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 20986, "output_tokens": 7506, "total_tokens": 28492, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 5888}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 6208}}}
